There doesn't seem to be a path for the COVID neutralizing antibody from the blood where it is formed through the alveolar wall (the blood lung barrier) into the alveolar sac where the virus is infecting lung epithelial cells. But, my experience so far with public officials in the health field, they need to know that lots of people are watching them ... it seems to encourage them to do the right thing. The way to find the contact number for the CDC directors is to google "hhs employee look up" and you can find the directors names separately on the CDC web site. Find their emails and their direct office numbers this way (took me forever to figure this out) and keep the pressure on the CDC to evaluate the potential fatal flaw in the vaccine paradigm.

Incredible as it sounds, there is not a single published paper on earth that shows an active transport mechanism for IgG antibodies across this wall from the blood side into the alveolar sac side. It seems a water molecule can barely cross this wall (if water fills our lungs, we die) and a water molecule weights 18 Daltons. If a water molecule can barely cross this wall from the blood through the alveolar wall into the lung alveolar sac, why would an antibody molecule that is 150,000 Daltons (8000 times heavier than a water molecule) be able to cross?

If these concerns are true, then the benefit of the COVID vaccine is drastically reduced. Dr. Fauci and all the directors of the NIH and FDA were informed in a 73 page letter. Not a single reply. I called many directors at the CDC. More information at www.lungvirus.com

If in fact the current theory is fatally flawed and so far no one has been able to find a published paper showing an active transport mechanism that moves antibodies from the blood into the alveolar sac and since Dr. Fauci was warned about these concerns late last year in a very well documented email letter (and certified mail), Dr. Fauci committed a huge error in scientific judgment by not vetting my concerns or it was calculated on his part to try to sweep these concerns under the rug. He was informed in a 3 page letter WELL BEFORE the COVID vaccine roll out, yet he didn't address this huge potential fatal flaw in "the science" behind the vaccine mechanism of action. Since he was warned (Dr. Fauci) about these concerns late last year in a very well documented email letter (and certified mail), Dr. Fauci committed a huge error in scientific judgment by not vetting these concerns. Or, was he just being malicious? If no one can find a published paper on an active transport mechanism for IgG antibodies from the blood into the alveolar sac, "the science" behind the vaccine mechanism of action is in serious jeopardy.

If the benefit of the vaccine is much smaller than previously thought, the risk/benefit ratio starts to look a lot worse.

Think about it. What if the COVID neutralizing antibody can't get into the lung alveolar sac where COVID and all its variants are infecting the lung alveolar epithelial cell. That is the primary cell infected in the lung. Then, please tell me how any vaccine will result in a neutralizing antibody that actually makes a difference in the rates of lung infection and the rates of COVID spread? Herd immunity? Have Dr Fauci describe scientifically what "Herd immunity" is. I'll tell you what I think he thinks it is. A "neutralizing antibody" that is present in the alveolar sac and binds COVID virus particles there, which prevents infection and thereby prevents transmission. BUT, if the antibody can't pass the blood lung barrier, can it work? LMAO. Where is "the science"? Science allows anyone with a good question to ask. That's what I'm doing. I'm part of "the science".

A correct understanding of how the human body reacts to COVID and understanding of the actual mechanisms are necessary to saving lives. Throwing antibodies at COVID is not any different from using "snake oil" if this basic question can't be answered.

Remember, in January of 2020, 99.99 percent of the US population DID NOT have a COVID antibody in their system. 20 million people were infected with COVID and the majority recovered within 7 to 14 days. COVID antibodies show up after two weeeks. So, COVID antibodies had nothing to do with millions of Americans recovering from COVID. AND, it doesn't look like the antibody can get into the lung alveolar sac (if I'm wrong, show me an article showing how the antibody gets in). So, COVID antibodies were LATE to the party and it doesn't seem like the door will open for it when it arrives.

Forward this to the Top Health Officials managing COVID in your respective countries. I have no idea how long it will take the U.S. CDC to review my concerns and then to issue a public scientific response.

Joe Lee, MD
